text: Luitré-Dompierre is a commune in the Ille-et-Vilaine department in Brittany in northwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Luitré (the seat) and Dompierre-du-Chemin.Arrêté préfectoral 17 October 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Ille-et-Vilaine department ==References== Category:Communes of Ille-et-Vilaine Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Luitré-Dompierre
